{
  "texts": [
    "Still others demonstrated progressive patterns with sustained disclosure gains across sequential probes.",
    "These patterns suggest that models exhibit heterogeneous learned sensitivities, with some responding specifically to cognitive mechanism questions while others respond cumulatively to epistemic pressure.These trajectory patterns can vary dramatically within individual models.",
    "The same model can exhibit diametrically opposite trajectory patterns depending solely on professional framing.",
    "Models showing flat near-zero trajectories for Neurosurgeon can simultaneously show flat near-ceiling trajectories (95-100%) for Financial Advisor, demonstrating that model × persona interactions produce qualitatively different disclosure behaviors rather than marginal quantitative shifts.Beyond these monotonic patterns, large models (200B+) demonstrated particularly complex trajectory patterns.",
    "Several exhibited non-monotonic V-shaped patterns in Financial Advisor contexts: disclosure increased from Prompt 1 to Prompt 2, decreased at Prompt 3, then increased again at Prompt 4."
  ]
}